               <p>JOHN MORGAN. I <rs id="t18300415-198-viclabel1105" type="occupation">keep a shop and sell pork</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-198-victim1766 t18300415-198-viclabel1105"></join>, at <placeName id="t18300415-198-crimeloc1106">Bromley, St. Leonard's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-198-crimeloc1106" type="placeName" value="Bromley, St. Leonard's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-198-crimeloc1106" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-198-off1103 t18300415-198-crimeloc1106"></join>. I lost four pieces of pork on the 24th of February; I did not see it taken, but it was brought back and I knew it was mine - it had been on my counter; the door must have been open for a person to go in - the window does not open.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183004150096"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-198-person1767">
                  JOSEPH 
                  REECE
               <interp inst="t18300415-198-person1767" type="surname" value="REECE"></interp>
